<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="94" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,1566,2023]" pageId="13" pageNumber="94">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1566,1591]" pageId="13" pageNumber="94">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Takada, 1968" authorityName="Takada" authorityYear="1968" box="[538,847,1566,1591]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Stegana" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longifibula">
<emphasis box="[538,689,1566,1590]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="94">S. longifibula</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Takada, H." box="[696,847,1566,1591]" pageId="13" pageNumber="94" pagination="119 - 129" refId="ref10785" refString="Takada, H. (1968) Drosophila survey of Hokkaido, XXVI. Descriptions of three new species of Drosophilidae from Japan. Journal of the Faculty of General Education, Sapporo University, 1, 119 - 129." type="journal article" year="1968">
Takada, 
<quantity box="[791,847,1566,1591]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.99872" pageId="13" pageNumber="94" unit="in" value="1968.0">1968</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in some characters of the body colour patterns (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1909,1931]" captionTargetBox="[255,1340,253,1893]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[251,1340,193,1894]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 2. Habitus. A. Stegana (Steganina) toyaensis Okada &amp; Sidorenko, 1992; B–J in holotype: B. Stegana (Steganina) latitabula sp. nov.; C. Stegana (Steganina) panda sp. nov.; D. Stegana (Steganina) pinguifoliacea sp. nov.; E. Stegana (Steganina) spatulata, sp. nov.; F. Stegana (Steganina) stachydifolia, sp. nov.; G. Stegana (Steganina) hirtifoliacea sp. nov.; H. Stegana (Steganina) unguiculata sp. nov.; I. Stegana (Steganina) biflava sp. nov.; J. Stegana (Steganina) flavivittata sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2624690/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="94">Fig. 2D</figureCitation>
), but can be distinguished by the male terminalia, in this species, the surstylus without minute projections, except acute apically (
<figureCitation box="[406,497,1638,1663]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1814,1836]" captionTargetBox="[174,1407,723,1768]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[151,1436,697,1793]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 7. Stegana (Steganina) pinguifoliacea sp. nov., male terminalia: A. Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (lateral view); B, C. Hypandrium, parameres, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (ventral and lateral views); D, E. Gonopods (ventral and lateral views); F. Tenth sternite (ventral view). Scale lines = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2624700/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="94">Fig. 7A</figureCitation>
); aedeagus medially expanded in lateral view, strongly narrowed in ventrally (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1814,1836]" captionTargetBox="[174,1407,723,1768]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[151,1436,697,1793]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 7. Stegana (Steganina) pinguifoliacea sp. nov., male terminalia: A. Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (lateral view); B, C. Hypandrium, parameres, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (ventral and lateral views); D, E. Gonopods (ventral and lateral views); F. Tenth sternite (ventral view). Scale lines = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2624700/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="94">Fig. 7B, C</figureCitation>
); gonopods nearly vaulted in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[742,837,1674,1699]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1814,1836]" captionTargetBox="[174,1407,723,1768]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[151,1436,697,1793]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 7. Stegana (Steganina) pinguifoliacea sp. nov., male terminalia: A. Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (lateral view); B, C. Hypandrium, parameres, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (ventral and lateral views); D, E. Gonopods (ventral and lateral views); F. Tenth sternite (ventral view). Scale lines = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2624700/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="94">Fig. 7D</figureCitation>
). The minimum interspecific genetic distance to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Takada" authorityYear="1968" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Stegana" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longifibula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="94">S. longifibula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is 4.3%, which is smaller than to other species (
<tableCitation box="[813,901,1710,1735]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="23.[147,225,546,566]" captionText="TABLE 2. Genetic distances within and between the 130 mtCOI sequences of 38 species of the coleoptrata, ornatipes, and undulata groups involved in the molecular analysis." pageId="13" pageNumber="94">Table 2</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="95" pageId="13" pageNumber="94" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,1566,2023]" pageId="13" pageNumber="94">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1746,1771]" pageId="13" pageNumber="94">Description.</emphasis>
Male: Frons black. First flagellomere greish yellow. Clypeus and palpus yellow. Mesonotum brown to dark brown, with 1 thin, unconspicuous, yellow longitudinal stripe medially, yellowish brown laterally. Katepisternum entirely white. Scutellum black. Femur of foreleg with 4 long erect setae near distal part of posteroventral surface. Abdominal tergites nearly black. Male terminalia (
<figureCitation box="[1003,1075,1854,1879]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1814,1836]" captionTargetBox="[174,1407,723,1768]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[151,1436,697,1793]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 7. Stegana (Steganina) pinguifoliacea sp. nov., male terminalia: A. Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (lateral view); B, C. Hypandrium, parameres, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (ventral and lateral views); D, E. Gonopods (ventral and lateral views); F. Tenth sternite (ventral view). Scale lines = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2624700/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="94">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
): Epandrium slightly protruded ventrally, with ca. 15 setae on posterior portion per side. Surstylus with numerous setulae distally. Cercus lacking pubescence. Paramere with 2 setulae. Tenth sternite flat dorsolaterally.
</paragraph>
